raft /rɑːft/

(rafts) 

1. N-COUNT A raft is a floating platform made from large pieces of wood or other materials tied together. 木排; 筏 

例： ...a river trip on bamboo rafts through dense rainforest. …一次乘着竹筏穿过茂密雨林的河上旅行。 

2. N-COUNT A raft is a small rubber or plastic boat that you blow air into to make it float. (橡皮或塑料的) 小型充气船 

例： The crew spent two days and nights in their raft. 船员们在他们的小充气船上度过了两天两夜。 

3. V to convey on or travel by raft, or make a raft from 筏运; 筏行; 制成筏 

4. N a large collection or amount 大量 [非正式] 

例： a raft of old notebooks discovered in a cupboard

